CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS AND ADMINISTRATIVE ACTIONS

June 8, 2007

[Cite as 06/08/2007 Case Announcements, 2007-Ohio-2780.]

MISCELLANEOUS ORDERS

In re Report of the Commission On Continuing Legal Education. Shirley Ann Kirkland (# 0023668), Respondent. CLE-1993-23668

ORDER

This matter originated in this court on the filing of a report by the Commission on Continuing Legal Education (“commission”) pursuant to Gov.Bar R. X(6)(A)(l)(b) and (A)(2)(d). The commission recommended the imposition of sanctions against certain attorneys, including the above-named respondent, for failure to comply with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. X, Attorney Continuing Legal Education, for the 1991-1992 reporting period.

On April 15, 1994, this court entered an order against respondent adopting the recommendation of the commission that respondent be ordered to pay a sanction in the amount of $150.00 for failure to comply with Gov.Bar R. X during the 1991-1992 reporting period.

On April 27, 2007, the commission filed a motion to vacate, requesting that the order of April 15, 1994, pertaining to the above-named respondent, be vacated. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motion to vacate is granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that the order of April 15, 1994 pertaining to

respondent is vacated, and this cause is dismissed.
